&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;We are looking for a Clinical Specialist to join our Medical AI team on a 50% part-time basis.&lt;br&gt;You will work at the intersection of medicine and AI, creating clinical datasets, evaluating AI-generated outputs, and providing clinical expertise throughout the product development process to help build safe and reliable healthcare AI solutions.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and validate high-quality clinical datasets for AI model development and evaluation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review AI-generated clinical outputs and provide structured clinical feedback.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform quality assurance on annotations and production cases.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to annotation guidelines, evaluation frameworks, and clinical documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Product, AI, and Engineering teams to improve AI products and clinical workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6th-year medical student or above (or medical school graduate).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong clinical knowledge and attention to detail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interest in AI and familiarity with LLMs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong written communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work independently and collaboratively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in medical annotation, clinical research, healthcare AI, or medical informatics is an advantage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Details&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;50% position (~20 hours/week).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hybrid role with at least one day per week in the office.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We Are:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Behind every leading health system is K Health’s AI-powered virtual care engine.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Esteemed health systems like Mayo Clinic, Cedars-Sinai, Mass General Brigham, Hackensack Meridian Health, and Hartford Healthcare partner with K Health to build and run modern primary virtual care clinics on their behalf.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our deeply integrated model modernizes the primary care loop by using AI to put humans first. For our patients, we offer clinical AI (i.e., PatientGPT) and unparalleled access to close care gaps around the clock. For our Providers, we deliver provider-serving agentic solutions (i.e., Perfect Note) to eliminate administrative overload and burnout. And for the health systems, we deploy our top-grade Virtualists in AI-powered virtual clinics 24/7 to capture the patients&#39; care journeys at step one, retain the journey through the system for longitudinal care, and strengthen profitability.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re founded in 2016, headquartered in New York City, and backed by nearly $400 million from leading investors including Valor Equity Partners, Claure Group, Mangrove Capital Partners, 14W, Notable Capital, Lerer Hippeau, Primary Venture Partners, Comcast Ventures, PICO Venture Partners, Max Ventures, and other strategic healthcare partners.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We offer competitive compensation packages based on industry benchmarks for function, level, and geographic location. Offer amounts are determined by multiple factors such as a candidate&#39;s experience and expertise.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We are proud to be an Equal Opportunity Employer and consider applicants for employment regardless of race, ethnicity, religion, color, national origin, ancestry, disability, medical condition, g

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an analytical and results-driven CRM Manager to join our dynamic Product team. You will own executing and optimizing CRM flows to convert leads and educate existing patients about our services. The ideal candidate will have a strong track record of hitting business goals by deeply understanding how to effectively message to key cohorts.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This role requires onsite presence in our New York City office 4 days a week and does not provide immigration support.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own strategy and execution on CRM automations and campaigns, including creative development and testing across email, SMS, push notifications, and in-app content&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and execute on audience segmentation strategies to enhance patient experience and creative messaging&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Data team to measure effectiveness across tactics and find opportunities to improve efficiency and/or scale&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create benchmarks and analyze campaign results to determine testing roadmap&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with Product and Engineering teams to ensure patients are receiving important information as we evolve our products and services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate key marketing initiatives and results to broader team and key external partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we&#39;re looking for:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4+ years of experience in CRM / lifecycle marketing in fast-paced environments with experience executing in Braze preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to hit business growth goals through strategic cohorting and insights-driven creative messaging and testing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Data and results-driven with strong ability to tell a story using data insights and performance results&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent problem-solving skills with track record of using data-driven approaches to solve complex business problems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication skills and experience working cross-functionally with internal creative, data, and product teams and external partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Desire to stay abreast of current CRM and broader marketing trends and best practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly motivated, detail-oriented, and a team player&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
