&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Senior Software Engineer at K Health, you are the champion of technical excellence for a high-stakes portfolio of clinical AI and a suite of products that serve the patients and the physicians. We don&#39;t just build apps; we build, and operate modern, AI-powered, 24/7 virtual clinics for the nation’s largest health systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, your mission is to architect a product ecosystem where reliability, privacy, and performance are non-negotiable. You will lead the development of reusable components and resilient architectures that exude trust, ensuring that every patient interaction is seamless and every clinical data point is secure. You will be a &quot;multiplier,&quot; creating the foundational frameworks that allow us to deploy 5-star experiences across a portfolio of partners without sacrificing the quality our users depend on.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This role requires onsite presence in our New York City office 4 days a week and does not provide immigration support.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Architect for Trust: Design and drive a unified product engineering strategy that supports a portfolio of products and solutions, prioritizing modularity, reusability, and extreme resiliency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full-Stack Ownership: Own the end-to-end lifecycle of products and features, from multi-platform clients, to the Kotlin/JVM-based backend services that power them.&lt;/li&gt;
